==English==
===Etymology===
From ''[[skeleton]]''
===Noun===
'''skell'''
#(''US'') a [[homeless]] person, especially one who sleeps in the [[New York]] [[subway]]
#(''US, informal police jargon'') a male suspicious person or crime suspect, especially a street person such as a drug dealer, pimp or panhandler. (Compare [[scumbag]].)  Popularized on the American TV police drama ''NYPD Blue''.